  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Cut the<strong>&nbsp;potatoes</strong> (skins on) lengthways into wedges</p>\r\n<p>Add them to a pot (with a matching lid) of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cook uncovered for 7-9 min or until fork-tender, then drain, return them to the pot and cover to keep warm until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-mustard-and-tarragon-chicken/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and quarter the <strong>shallots</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-mustard-and-tarragon-chicken/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>shallots</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3 min or until starting to brown</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-mustard-and-tarragon-chicken/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>diced chicken</strong> to a bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>flour</strong> and mix to coat thoroughly</p>\r\n<p>Dissolve the <strong>stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-mustard-and-tarragon-chicken/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>floured</strong>&nbsp;<strong>chicken</strong> and<strong> garlic</strong> to the <strong>shallots</strong> and cook for 3 min or until starting to brown</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>tarragon</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-mustard-and-tarragon-chicken/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> stock</strong> and half the<strong> tarragon</strong> to the pan</p>\r\n<p>Reduce the heat to medium-low, cover with a lid and cook for a further 5 min or until the chicken is cooked through</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-mustard-and-tarragon-chicken/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Stir&nbsp;the <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> and half <span class=\"text-danger\">[all]&nbsp;</span>the <strong>cr&egrave;me fra&icirc;che</strong> into the cooked chicken and cook for a further min until just warmed through</p>\r\n<p>Once warmed, remove from the heat and stir in the remaining <strong>tarragon</strong></p>\r\n<p>Taste for seasoning, adding <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-mustard-and-tarragon-chicken/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the creamy chicken over the potatoes</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
